		<title>Habits</title>
		<link>https://llgt.cafe/habits</link>
					<comments>https://llgt.cafe/habits#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[llgt]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 29 Oct 2022 21:05:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LLGT]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://llgt.cafe/?p=33</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[I started something different about a week ago. I was listening to “Atomic Habits” by James Clear and decided that I wanted to work on some of my own habits. On an index card, I wrote down a list of things that I would like&#160;<a class="read-more" href="https://llgt.cafe/habits">&#8230;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>I started something different about a week ago. I was listening to “Atomic Habits” by James Clear and decided that I wanted to work on some of my own habits.</p>



<p>On an index card, I wrote down a list of things that I would like to start doing on a daily basis. I keep it where I can easily see it. On a dry erase board, I have the word “Habits” written. Each time I do one of the things on my list, I put a small box. I had thought about using candies, moving them from one container to another whenever I did something on my list, but this seemed counterproductive. It’s sort of like given myself a gold star.</p>



<p>I have to admit that I had hoped that this system would work for a couple of habits that I would like to break. Sadly, it hasn&#8217;t.</p>



<p>According to Clear, it’s a good idea to start small. It’s better to take one step, workout for three minutes, or floss one tooth until it becomes a daily routine. My list includes push-ups  (I do three of them), walking ten minutes a day — weather permitting — and writing in my journal. I have drawing on my list, but stopped that habit after a couple of days.</p>



<p>You might like to try something similar. Or, maybe you have your own system. If so, I’d love to hear about it.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
